User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Macintosh; U; Intel Mac OS X 10.6; en-US; rv:1.9.1.18) Gecko/20110320 SeaMonkey/2.0.13
Build Identifier: Firefox 4.0, SeaMonkey 2.0.13, Camino 2.0.7

I use a Bookmarks Bar folder including Clickability's EMAIL THIS, a javascript call <javascript:(function()%7Bvar%20w=window;%20var%20popup;%20var%20clickURL=(self.clickURL)?self.clickURL:location.href;%20var%20clickTitle=(self.clickTitle)?self.clickTitle:document.title;%20void(popup%20=%20open('http://www.emailthis.clickability.com/et/emailThis?clickMap=createBB&url='+encodeURIComponent(clickURL)+'&title='+encodeURIComponent(clickTitle)+'&random='+Math.random(),'click','height=450,width=510,title=no,location=no,scrollbars=yes,menubars=no,toolbars=no,resizable=yes'));%20w.setTimeout(function()%7Bpopup.focus();%7D,250)%7D)();>. The send to and BCC and comments windows open, but the distorted strings of characters that have to be matched never loads.

If there is still an option to send you a graphic image, I will include it to show what happens in Safari vs. these three Mozilla apps.

Reproducible: Always

Steps to Reproduce:
1.Have an open web page and already have Clickability's EMAIL THIS available.
2.Select "EMAIL THIS" from the bookmarks bar or wherever you stuck it.
3.Observe that there are never any images in the bottom box.

Actual Results:  
The distorted images never show, therefore it is impossible to send the link to anyone.

Expected Results:  
The images would appear, the user matches them and hits Send and the link is on its way.

Although this happens now on a Mac Pro 10.6.7 w/10GB RAM, it also happened under earlier versions of OS X on this machine and on my earlier G3 (replaced in Nov of 2008).
comments.creator: whldorsey@hotmail.com
